<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-05-29T05:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-05-29T05:00:00-05:00" n="1170" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1170">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.48/121</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Germany</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_GJW1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Gerard</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Berlin</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-05-29T12:00:00+02:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">May 29, 1916, 12 noon</hi>
                                    </date>.<lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received May 30, 12.30 p.
                                        m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>3929. Your 3028, May 24, 6 p. m. Furnished copy of memorandum to the
                                Minister of Interior, <persName corresp="#p_HK1">Helfferich</persName>, to whom Chancellor referred me
                                personally four days ago. Talked over matter with <persName corresp="#p_HK1">Helfferich</persName> yesterday. Expect formal
                                answer soon, probably rejecting proposition. Have arranged
                                conference to-day with representatives of Foreign Office, Minister
                                of the Interior, and requested the disposition of
                                representatives.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_GJW1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gerard</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>